@localUrl=http://localhost:8000
@liveUrl=https://hrms.sysnovix.com/api

@admin_card=100001.1
@compc=1
@brnch=1

### ============================================================================
### RECRUITMENT MODULE (PART B: AI CV SCREENING & EVALUATION)
### ============================================================================

#* [x]
### 1. Upload CV to Talent Pool (No job_id)
# 🔍 CHECK: Python watcher should process the PDF in EMP_DOCS/1/1/RECRUITMENT_CVS/pool
# 🔍 CHECK DB: RECRUITMENT_CANDIDATES table for a new entry (metrics extracted by AI).
POST {{localUrl}}/recruitment/candidates/upload-cvs?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}&compc={{compc}}&brnch={{brnch}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="resume.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./resume.pdf
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 2. Check CV Status  #* [x]
# 🔍 CHECK: This returns the current processing state (queued, processed)
GET {{localUrl}}/recruitment/candidates/cv-status?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}&compc={{compc}}&brnch={{brnch}}&files=john_doe_pool.pdf


### 3. Direct CV File Upload for an Existing Candidate #* [x]
# 🔍 CHECK: PDF is queued in AI dropzone (pool or job_id dir) with _scope.json sidecar.
# 🔍 CHECK: Python watcher picks up file and auto-updates AI metrics & profile details.
@candidateId = 36
POST {{localUrl}}/recruitment/candidates/{{candidateId}}/cv?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="existing_cand.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./resume.pdf
--boundary--



### 4. Download Candidate CV
# 🔍 CHECK: The PDF file should be downloaded successfully #* [X] 
# Needs to follow proper folder struture to inserd pdf (works only here due to luck and manuel organization)
GET {{localUrl}}/recruitment/candidates/{{candidateId}}/cv?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}&inline=true

###  #* [x]
GET {{liveUrl}}/recruitment/candidates/{{candidateId}}/cv?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}&inline=true


### 5. Apply Pool Candidate to a Job   #* [x]
# 🔍 CHECK: RECRUITMENT_APPLICATIONS for new APP_ID. 
# 🔍 CHECK: Background task triggers; RECRUITMENT_AI_EVALUATIONS should get a new row.
@jobId = 105
POST {{localUrl}}/recruitment/candidates/{{candidateId}}/apply?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "job_id": {{jobId}},
    "source": "Internal Talent Pool"
}


### 6. Get Application AI Evaluation #* [x]
# 🔍 CHECK: Returns JSON of the AI evaluation (compatibility, score, strengths, weaknesses)
# Requires a valid appId that has been evaluated.
@appId = 71
GET {{localUrl}}/recruitment/applications/{{appId}}/evaluation?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}

### [x]
GET {{liveUrl}}/recruitment/applications/{{appId}}/evaluation?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}


### 7. Upload CV Directly for a Job #* [x]
# 🔍 CHECK: EMP_DOCS/1/1/RECRUITMENT_CVS/105 should get the PDF
# Watcher will parse AND score it against the job, creating a candidate & application automatically. 
POST {{localUrl}}/recruitment/candidates/upload-cvs?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}&job_id={{jobId}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="jane_smith_job.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./resume.pdf
--boundary--


### 8. Match Candidates Deep #* [x]
# 🔍 CHECK: Triggers AI evaluation for ALL candidates in pool against this job
POST {{localUrl}}/recruitment/jobs/{{jobId}}/match?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}&deep=true&top=5


### 9. Top Candidates Shortlist #* [x]
# 🔍 CHECK: Returns candidates ranked by their AI_SCORE
GET {{localUrl}}/recruitment/jobs/{{jobId}}/top-candidates?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}&top_k=5

### 9. Top Candidates Shortlist (Live) #* [x]
GET {{liveUrl}}/recruitment/jobs/{{jobId}}/top-candidates?admin_card_no={{admin_card}}&top_k=5